{
  "texts": [
    "Stimuli and interview strategies in SR.",
    "The rapid diffusion of Information and Communication Technology (ICT) and the exponential growth of online learning have brought new challenges and opportunities for using SR in educational research and in teaching and learning.",
    "Integrating ICT into education requires a careful selection of stimuli that can adapt to the constantly evolving learning environments.",
    "When applied in physical environments, audio or video stimuli respond favorably to interactions between teachers and students, enabling subsequent interviews to investigate their inner impressions or perceptions (Chu and Zhai, 2023).",
    "In contrast, educational activities incorporating digital technologies are not easily observable, with instructional behaviors conducted through electronic devices and in video or audio conference systems."
  ]
}